This paper is about exploring the regularity of sparse structure in convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG). The paper also discusses the impact of sparsity on hardware acceleration, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and neural engineering (NE). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on a sparse convolutional neural network accelerator (SCNN), which is related to computer architecture (AR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.AR.
